Minimal Stability Condition

Let:

C(t) = I_{model}(t) - I_{observed}(t)

Then stability requires:

\Delta \|C(t)\| \leq 0


---

Summary

The Paper–Desk–Lens–Loop system defines a minimal physical cognition loop.

It is:

observable

reproducible

non-abstract

compatible with feedback systems



---

One-Line Definition

A cognition system is stable when information, structure, perception, and iteration remain coherently coupled over time.


